  "optimization_hints": [
    "Q1: Parallel scan+aggregate on lineitem (60M rows). Zone-map pruning on l_shipdate. Low-cardinality GROUP BY (6 groups) → sorted aggregation. No sort needed (key order).",
    "Q2: Selective part filter (p_size=15, LIKE %BRASS ~5%). Correlated subquery decorrelation: materialize min(ps_supplycost) per region. Semi-join on region='EUROPE'.",
    "Q3: Multi-way hash join (customer→orders→lineitem). Filter early (c_mktsegment=20%, o_orderdate 48%). High-cardinality GROUP BY (1M groups) → hash aggregation + partial agg. Top-10 sort.",
    "Q4: Selective date range (25%). Semi-join EXISTS (lineitem with predicate). Low-cardinality GROUP BY (5 groups) → sorted agg.",
    "Q5: 6-way join with regional filters (ASIA=20%). Partial aggregation before global merge. ~1M output rows.",
    "Q6: Aggressive filters (shipdate 16.7%, discount 3%, quantity 48%). Vectorized filtering with SIMD. Aggregate single SUM(l_extendedprice*discount).",
    "Q7: Subquery materialization (filter supplier/customer pairs by nation). Low-cardinality GROUP BY (8 groups). Self-join on nation names.",
    "Q8: Complex filter chain (part type, region, date range). Subquery aggregation. Low-cardinality GROUP BY (2-3 groups).",
    "Q9: 6-way join with name pattern (LIKE %green%). Medium cardinality GROUP BY (25-50 groups). Profit calculation with supply cost.",
    "Q10: Selective filters (date 25%, returnflag='R'). Join+aggregate (1M customers). Top-20 sort.",
    "Q11: Selective filter (nation='GERMANY'). HAVING clause with subquery. Hash aggregation then filter.",
    "Q12: Time-range filter (1 year) on receipt_date. Low-cardinality GROUP BY (2 groups) by shipmode. CASE expressions in aggregate.",
    "Q13: LEFT OUTER JOIN customer→orders. High-cardinality GROUP BY (order counts). Two-level aggregation.",
    "Q14: Simple scan lineitem+part (filter shipdate 1-month window). Conditional SUM (CASE). Single aggregate computation.",
    "Q15: CTE materialization (3-month lineitem aggregate). Correlated subquery to find max revenue supplier. Final join.",
    "Q16: Multi-key filter (brand, type, size IN list). Subquery anti-join on s_suppkey. Medium-cardinality GROUP BY (1K+ groups).",
    "Q17: Correlated subquery (per-part average quantity). Selective join (brand+container). Single aggregate computation.",
    "Q18: Subquery IN (l_orderkey with HAVING >300 quantity). Selective join customer→orders→lineitem. Top-100.",
    "Q19: Complex OR predicates across 3 brand/container combinations. Selective lineitem+part. Single revenue SUM.",
    "Q20: Nested subqueries (part name, partsupp availability filter, lineitem subquery). Materialize inner results.",
    "Q21: Complex EXISTS/NOT EXISTS logic with lineitem self-joins. Selective filters (nation='SAUDI ARABIA'). Top-100.",
    "Q22: Correlated subquery on avg(c_acctbal). String extraction (SUBSTRING). Low-cardinality GROUP BY (7 country codes)."
  ],
  "summary": "TPC-H SF10: 60M-row lineitem (fact table) with 8 dimension tables. Dominant patterns: date range filters (Q1,Q3,Q5,Q6,Q12,Q14), multi-table joins (Q2,Q5,Q7,Q8,Q9,Q10), and hash aggregations (low-cardinality in 10/22 queries). Bottleneck: Q3,Q5,Q9 involve 5-6 table joins + high-cardinality aggregations. Key levers: (1) Parallel hash join on lineitem (32 cores, morsel-driven), (2) Zone-map pruning on l_shipdate/o_orderdate (selective filters), (3) Semi-join/subquery decorrelation (Q2,Q11,Q15,Q21), (4) Vectorized filtering + SIMD on lineitem predicates (Q1,Q6), (5) Sorted aggregation for low-cardinality GROUP BY keys (Q1,Q4,Q12)."
